  70,23,consistently performing their prayers
  70,24,and who give the rightful share of their wealth
  70,25,to the beggar and the poor
  70,26,and who ňĻfirmlyňļ believe in the Day of Judgment
  70,27,and those who fear the punishment of their Lord‚ÄĒ
  70,28,ňĻknowing thatňļ none should feel secure from their Lord‚Äôs punishment‚ÄĒ
  70,29,and those who guard their chastity
  70,30,"except with their wives or those ňĻbondwomenňļ in their possession,¬†for then they are free from blame"
  70,31,but whoever seeks beyond that are the transgressors
  70,32,ňĻThe faithful areňļ also those who are true to their trusts and covenants
  70,33,and who are honest in their testimony
  70,34,and who are ňĻproperlyňļ observant of their prayers
  70,35,"These will be in Gardens, held in honour"
  70,36,So what is the matter with the disbelievers that they rush ňĻhead-longňļ towards you ňĻO Prophetňļ
  70,37,"from the right and the left, in groups ňĻto mock youňļ"
  70,38,Does every one of them expect to be admitted into a Garden of Bliss
  70,39,"But no! Indeed, they ňĻalreadyňļ know what We created them from"
  70,40,"So, I do swear by the Lord of ňĻallňļ the points of sunrise and sunset¬†that We are truly capable"
  70,41,"of replacing them with ňĻothersňļ better than them, and We cannot be prevented ňĻfrom doing soňļ"
  70,42,"So let them indulge ňĻin falsehoodňļ and amuse ňĻthemselvesňļ until they face their Day, which they have been threatened with‚ÄĒ"
  70,43,"the Day they will come forth from the graves swiftly, as if racing to an idol ňĻfor a blessingňļ"
  70,44,"with eyes downcast, utterly covered with disgrace. That is the Day they have ňĻalwaysňļ been warned of"
  71,1,"Indeed, We sent Noah to his people ňĻsaying to himňļ, ‚ÄúWarn your people before a painful punishment comes to them.‚ÄĚ"
  71,2,"Noah proclaimed, ‚ÄúO my people! I am truly sent to you with a clear warning"
  71,3,"worship Allah ňĻaloneňļ, fear Him, and obey me"
  71,4,"He will forgive your sins, and delay your end until the appointed time.¬†Indeed, when the time set by Allah comes, it cannot be delayed, if only you knew!‚ÄĚ"
  71,5,"He cried, ‚ÄúMy Lord! I have surely called my people day and night"
  71,6,but my calls only made them run farther away
  71,7,"And whenever I invite them to be forgiven by You, they press their fingers into their ears, cover themselves with their clothes, persist ňĻin denialňļ, and act very arrogantly"
  71,8,Then I certainly called them openly
  71,9,then I surely preached to them publicly and privately
  71,10,"saying, ‚ÄėSeek your Lord‚Äôs forgiveness, ňĻforňļ He is truly Most Forgiving"
  71,11,He will shower you with abundant rain
  71,12,"supply you with wealth and children, and give you gardens as well as rivers"
  71,13,What is the matter with you that you are not in awe of the Majesty of Allah
  71,14,when He truly created you in stages ňĻof developmentňļ
  71,15,"Do you not see how Allah created seven heavens, one above the other"
  71,16,"placing the moon within them as a ňĻreflectedňļ light, and the sun as a ňĻradiantňļ lamp"
  71,17,Allah ňĻaloneňļ caused you¬†to grow from the earth like a plant
  71,18,"Then He will return you to it, and then simply bring you forth ňĻagainňļ"
  71,19,And Allah ňĻaloneňļ spread out the earth for you
  71,20,to walk along its spacious pathways.‚Äô‚ÄĚ
  71,21,"ňĻEventually,ňļ Noah cried, ‚ÄúMy Lord! They have certainly persisted in disobeying me, and followed ňĻinsteadňļ those ňĻeliteňļ whose ňĻabundantňļ wealth and children only increase them in loss"
  71,22,and who have devised a tremendous plot
  71,23,"urging ňĻtheir followersňļ, ‚ÄėDo not abandon your idols‚ÄĒespecially Wadd, Suw√Ę‚Äô, Yagh√Ľth, Ya‚Äô√Ľq, and Nasr.‚Äô"
  71,24,"Those ňĻeliteňļ have already led many astray. So ňĻO Lordňļ, only allow the wrongdoers to stray farther away.‚ÄĚ"
  71,25,"So because of their sins, they were drowned, then admitted into the Fire. And they found none to help them against Allah"
  71,26,"Noah had prayed, ‚ÄúMy Lord! Do not leave a single disbeliever on earth"
  71,27,"For if You spare ňĻany ofňļ them, they will certainly mislead Your servants, and give birth only to ňĻwickedňļ sinners, staunch disbelievers"
  71,28,"My Lord! Forgive me, my parents, and whoever enters my house in faith, and ňĻallňļ believing men and women. And increase the wrongdoers only in destruction.‚ÄĚ"
  72,1,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúIt has been revealed to me that a group of jinn listened ňĻto the Quran,ňļ and said ňĻto their fellow jinnňļ: ‚ÄėIndeed, we have heard a wondrous recitation"
  72,2,"It leads to Right Guidance so we believed in it, and we will never associate anyone with our Lord ňĻin worshipňļ"
  72,3,"ňĻNow, we believe thatňļ our Lord‚ÄĒExalted is His Majesty‚ÄĒhas neither taken a mate nor offspring"
  72,4,and that the foolish of us used to utter ňĻoutrageousňļ falsehoods about Allah
  72,5,We certainly thought that humans and jinn would never speak lies about Allah
  72,6,And some men used to seek refuge with some jinn‚ÄĒso they increased each other in wickedness
  72,7,"And those ňĻhumansňļ thought, just like you ňĻjinnňļ, that Allah would not resurrect anyone ňĻfor judgmentňļ"
  72,8,"ňĻEarlierňļ we tried to reach heaven ňĻfor newsňļ, only to find it filled with stern guards and shooting stars"
  72,9,"We used to take up positions there for eavesdropping, but whoever dares eavesdrop now will find a flare¬†lying in wait for them"
  72,10,"Now, we have no clue whether evil is intended for those on earth, or their Lord intends for them what is right"
  72,11,Among us are those who are righteous and those who are less so. We have been of different factions
  72,12,"ňĻNow,ňļ we truly know that we cannot frustrate Allah on earth, nor can we escape from Him ňĻinto heavenňļ"
  72,13,"When we heard the guidance ňĻof the Quranňļ, we ňĻreadilyňļ believed in it. For whoever believes in their Lord will have no fear of being denied ňĻa rewardňļ or wronged"
  72,14,"And among us are those who have submitted ňĻto Allahňļ and those who are deviant. So ňĻas forňļ those who submitted, it is they who have attained Right Guidance"
  72,15,"And as for the deviant, they will be fuel for Hell.‚Äô‚ÄĚ"
  72,16,"Had the deniers followed the Right Way, We would have certainly granted them abundant rain to drink‚ÄĒ"
  72,17,as a test for them.¬†And whoever turns away from the remembrance of their Lord will be admitted by Him into an overwhelming punishment
  72,18,"The places of worship are ňĻonlyňļ for Allah, so do not invoke anyone besides Him"
  72,19,"Yet when the servant of Allah¬†stood up calling upon Him ňĻaloneňļ, the pagans almost swarmed over him"
  72,20,"Say, ňĻO Prophet,ňļ ‚ÄúI call only upon my Lord, associating none with Him ňĻin worshipňļ.‚ÄĚ"
  72,21,"Say, ‚ÄúIt is not in my power to harm or benefit you.‚ÄĚ"
  72,22,"Say, ‚ÄúNo one can protect me from Allah ňĻif I were to disobey Himňļ, nor can I find any refuge other than Him"
  72,23,"ňĻMy duty isňļ only to convey ňĻthe truthňļ from Allah and ňĻdeliverňļ His messages.‚ÄĚ And whoever disobeys Allah and His Messenger will certainly be in the Fire of Hell, to stay there for ever and ever"
  72,24,Only when they see what they have been threatened with will they know who is weaker in helpers and inferior in manpower
  72,25,"Say, ‚ÄúI do not know if what you are promised is near or my Lord has set a distant time for it"
  72,26,"ňĻHe is theňļ Knower of the unseen, disclosing none of it to anyone"
  72,27,except messengers of His choice. Then He appoints angel-guards before and behind them
  72,28,"to ensure that the messengers fully deliver the messages of their Lord‚ÄĒthough He ňĻalreadyňļ knows all about them, and keeps account of everything.‚ÄĚ"
  73,1,O you wrapped ňĻin your clothesňļ
  73,2,Stand all night ňĻin prayerňļ except a little‚ÄĒ
