  73,4,or a little more‚ÄĒand recite the Quran ňĻproperlyňļ in a measured way
  73,5,ňĻForňļ We will soon send upon you a weighty revelation
  73,6,"Indeed, worship in the night is more impactful and suitable for recitation"
  73,7,For during the day you are over-occupied ňĻwith worldly dutiesňļ
  73,8,"ňĻAlwaysňļ remember the Name of your Lord, and devote yourself to Him wholeheartedly"
  73,9,"ňĻHe is theňļ Lord of the east and the west. There is no god ňĻworthy of worshipňļ except Him, so take Him ňĻaloneňļ as a Trustee of Affairs"
  73,10,"Be patient ňĻO Prophetňļ with what they say, and depart from them courteously"
  73,11,And leave to Me the deniers‚ÄĒthe people of luxury‚ÄĒand bear with them for a little while
  73,12,"ňĻForňļ We certainly have shackles, a ňĻragingňļ Fire"
  73,13,"choking food, and a painful punishment ňĻin store for themňļ"
  73,14,"on the Day the earth and mountains will shake ňĻviolentlyňļ, and mountains will be ňĻreduced toňļ dunes of shifting sand"
  73,15,"Indeed, We have sent to you a messenger as a witness over you, just as We sent a messenger to Pharaoh"
  73,16,"But Pharaoh disobeyed the messenger, so We seized him with a stern grip"
  73,17,"If you ňĻpagansňļ persist in disbelief, then how will you guard yourselves against ňĻthe horrors ofňļ a Day which will turn children‚Äôs hair grey"
  73,18,It will ňĻevenňļ cause the sky to split apart. His promise ňĻof judgmentňļ must be fulfilled
